         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/6/84 ¶  ¶ It is a long time, dear Dr Beccari, since I wrote to you; and you must have deemed it strange, that I did not send you a return consignment of museum-plants for the nice lot of Sunda Isla...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.06.21a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/6/84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is a long time, dear Dr Beccari, since I wrote to you; and you must have deemed it strange, that I did not send you a return consignment of museum-plants for the nice lot of Sunda Island plants, received from you.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to O. Beccari, 12 March 1882<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 82-03-12a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The fact is, that I long since intended to do so, but the incessant calls on my ill supported Department for the various Exhibitions ("Expositions") and other extrawork left me no time, especially as I also acquired for the Victorian Government the very extensive Sonderian collections,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to L. Smith, 16 February 1882, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Short (1990).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to be put in order for Museum-purposes, and some publications had to be carried on in reference to Australian plants irrespective of the enormous correspondence. I am now however somewhat better placed for assistance as regards<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Herbarium"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>work, and several sets of spare-specimens are under preparation, one of which will be despatched to you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>And now, my dear Doctor, I would beg of you, whether you can let me have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">some</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">New Guinea plants for elaboration.</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Australia is almost exhausted, and I have during two years had but extremely few novelties from all Australia. I am therefore eager to participate in your New Guinean treasures, and should like to write a chapter for your splendid<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Malesia".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The fact, that this work evidently does not get the literary help from your confreres, which it deserves, gives me courage to ask you for some of your Mt Arfak<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>West Papua, Indonesia.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plants &amp;c, such as you do not care to elaborate yourself, especially as Mr Forbes<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Forbes.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is proceeding now to New Guinea and may rediscover some of your undescribed species. If I had the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">second</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>set of any Papuan plants, which you wish to entrust to me, I would not long keep it here and return it to you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Marquis Toverena and his Lady continue my kindest friends, and we often speak of you and Signor D'Albertis,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Almost certainly Luigi Maria d'Albertis.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to whom I wish to be remembered with all friendliness.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Any plants sent to my Agents, Mess Watson &amp; Scull, Lower Thames Street,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. London.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would be forwarded without expense to you.</p>
         </div>
